      "data": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A hail of rock-hard ice pounds to the ground in a 20-foot-radius, 40-foot-high cylinder centered on a point within range. Each creature in the cylinder must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 2d8]] bludgeoning damage and [[/r 4d6]] cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Hailstones turn the storm's area of effect into difficult terrain until the end of your next turn.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"5679\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the bludgeoning damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 4th.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
